## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design a pluggable, runtime-extensible command system for a GUI, mirroring IDE plugins like VS Code.

## Key Concepts
- Command pattern and type-safe interfaces
- Runtime plugin/registry architecture
- Conflict resolution strategies (override, error, namespacing)
- Lazy canExecute evaluation and cancellation propagation

## Code Example
```typescript
interface Command {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  execute(): Promise<void> | void;
  shortcut?: string;
  category?: string;
  canExecute?: () => boolean;
}

type ConflictStrategy = 'override' | 'error' | 'namespace';

class CommandRegistry {
  private commands = new Map<string, Command>();
  private strategy: ConflictStrategy = 'override';

  constructor(strategy: ConflictStrategy = 'override') {
    this.strategy = strategy;
  }

  register(command: Command): void {
    if (this.commands.has(command.id)) {
      if (this.strategy === 'error') {
        throw new Error(`Command "${command.id}" already registered`);
      }
      if (this.strategy === 'namespace') {
        command.id = `${command.category || 'default'}:${command.id}`;
      }
    }
    this.commands.set(command.id, command);
  }

  unregister(id: string): boolean {
    return this.commands.delete(id);
  }

  get(id: string): Command | undefined {
    return this.commands.get(id);
  }

  getAll(): Command[] {
    return Array.from(this.commands.values());
  }

  getByCategory(category: string): Command[] {
    return this.getAll().filter(c => c.category === category);
  }

  async execute(id: string, signal?: AbortSignal): Promise<void> {
    const cmd = this.commands.get(id);
    if (!cmd) throw new Error(`Command "${id}" not found`);
    if (cmd.canExecute && !cmd.canExecute()) {
      throw new Error(`Command "${id}" cannot execute`);
    }
    await cmd.execute();
  }
}

// Usage
const registry = new CommandRegistry();

registry.register({
  id: 'save',
  title: 'Save Document',
  category: 'File',
  shortcut: 'Ctrl+S',
  canExecute: () => hasUnsavedChanges,
  execute: async () => { /* save logic */ }
});

registry.register({
  id: 'git:commit',
  title: 'Git Commit',
  category: 'Version Control',
  execute: () => { /* commit logic */ }
});
```

## Key Design Decisions
- **Lazy evaluation**: canExecute is invoked immediately before execution, enabling dynamic state checks
- **Cancellation**: AbortController/signal support allows long-running commands to be cancelled
- **Flexible conflict resolution**: Strategy pattern accommodates different plugin ecosystems
- **Type safety**: TypeScript ensures commands expose required properties at compile time

