## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates your understanding of runtime extensibility, concurrency safety, and clean separation between core rendering logic and plugin points.

## Key Concepts
- **Runtime plugin registry**: A centralized map that stores helper factories, enabling registration without engine rebuilds
- **Template compilation**: Templates are parsed into an intermediate representation that makes runtime calls to resolved helpers
- **Scope isolation**: Distinguish between global helpers (available to all templates) and per-template helpers (isolated to specific template instances)
- **Error handling**: Graceful degradation when helpers are missing, with clear error messages and optional fallback behavior
- **Thread safety**: Considerations for concurrent access in multi-threaded environments

## Code Example
```typescript
type HelperFn = (arg: string, ctx: Record<string, unknown>) => string;
type HelperFactory = () => HelperFn;

class HelperRegistry {
  private store = new Map<string, HelperFactory>();

  register(name: string, factory: HelperFactory): void {
    this.store.set(name, factory);
  }

  resolve(name: string): HelperFn {
    const factory = this.store.get(name);
    if (!factory) {
      throw new Error(`Helper '${name}' not found`);
    }
    return factory();
  }

  has(name: string): boolean {
    return this.store.has(name);
  }
}

// Usage
const registry = new HelperRegistry();

registry.register('uppercase', () => (s) => s.toUpperCase());
registry.register('dateFormat', () => (s, ctx) => 
  new Date(s).toLocaleDateString(ctx.locale ?? 'en-US'));
registry.register('currency', () => (s, ctx) => 
  Number(s).toLocaleString(ctx.currency ?? 'USD', { style: 'currency', currency: ctx.currency ?? 'USD' }));

// Render example
function render(template: string, ctx: Record<string, unknown>, registry: HelperRegistry): string {
  return template.replace(/\{\{(\w+)\s+(.+?)\}\}/g, (_, helper, arg) => {
    try {
      return registry.resolve(helper)(arg, ctx);
    } catch (e) {
      return `[Error: ${(e as Error).message}]`;
    }
  });
}

// Example: {{uppercase hello}}, {{dateFormat 2024-01-15}}, {{currency 99.99}}
```

## Scope Considerations
- **Global helpers**: Registered once on the shared registry; all templates can access them. Use when helpers are universally applicable.
- **Per-template helpers**: Passed at render time or scoped to specific template instances. Use when helpers need isolation or template-specific behavior.

## Error Handling
- Throw descriptive errors for missing helpers
- Provide a `has()` method for optional fallback logic
- Consider wrapping render errors to continue processing other placeholders

## Thread Safety
- Use immutable snapshots or copy-on-write for concurrent reads
- Employ mutexes (e.g., `ReadWriteLock`) for registration during runtime
- In single-threaded JS environments, the registry is naturally safe; focus on clean async handling for worker threads

## Why This Is Asked

This question evaluates your ability to design a plug-in style, runtime-extensible CLI using classic design patterns with a minimal surface area.

## Key Concepts

- **Registry Pattern**: Maps command names to factories for dynamic lookup
- **Factory Pattern**: Creates command instances on demand
- **Dispatcher**: Resolves and executes commands with provided arguments
- **Conflict Handling**: Strategy-based approach (overwrite, warn, or reject)
- **Help Generation**: Aggregates help() output from all registered commands

## Code Example

```typescript
interface Command {
  execute(args: string[]): Promise<any>;
  help(): string;
}

type CommandFactory = () => Command;

class CommandRegistry {
  private factories = new Map<string, CommandFactory>();

  register(name: string, factory: CommandFactory, allowOverwrite = false): void {
    if (this.factories.has(name) && !allowOverwrite) {
      throw new Error(`Command '${name}' already registered`);
    }
    this.factories.set(name, factory);
  }

  getFactory(name: string): CommandFactory | undefined {
    return this.factories.get(name);
  }

  getAllCommands(): string[] {
    return Array.from(this.factories.keys());
  }
}

class Dispatcher {
  constructor(private registry: CommandRegistry) {}

  async dispatch(name: string, args: string[]): Promise<any> {
    const factory = this.registry.getFactory(name);
    if (!factory) {
      throw new Error(`Unknown command: ${name}`);
    }
    return factory().execute(args);
  }

  help(): string {
    const commands = this.registry.getAllCommands();
    return commands.map(name => {
      const factory = this.registry.getFactory(name)!;
      return factory().help();
