## Why This Is Asked
Assesses the ability to apply the Command pattern with a runtime registry for runtime extensibility, decoupling command invocation from implementation.

## Key Concepts
- Command pattern for encapsulating each request as an object
- Runtime extensibility through dynamic registration
- Isolation and error handling for fault tolerance
- Async execution for non-blocking operations

## Code Example
```typescript
interface Command {
  name: string;
  execute(args: unknown): Promise<void>;
}

type CommandFactory = () => Command;

class CommandRegistry {
  private map = new Map<string, CommandFactory>();

  register(name: string, factory: CommandFactory): void {
    this.map.set(name, factory);
  }

  async execute(name: string, args: unknown): Promise<void> {
    const factory = this.map.get(name);
    if (!factory) throw new Error(`Unknown command: ${name}`);
    const command = factory();
    try {
      await command.execute(args);
