registry.register('init', () => new InitCommand());
registry.register('build', () => new BuildCommand());
registry.register('deploy', () => new DeployCommand());
await registry.execute('build', { target: 'prod' });
```

## Design Pattern
The **Command pattern** is ideal here because it encapsulates each operation as an executable object, enabling delayed execution, queuing, and undo functionality if needed.

## Trade-offs
- **Pros**: Loose coupling, runtime extensibility, easy testing (mock commands)
- **Cons**: Additional indirection, slightly more complex codebase, registry can become a global state hotspot

