  - *Pipeline*: Centralized orchestration, easy to add/remove stages, simpler error aggregation, but rules have less control over flow
  - *Chain of Responsibility*: Rules can decide to pass or halt, more flexible branching logic, but harder to reorder dynamically and error handling is distributed
